name: SALT
tweet: “#Culture usually eats strategy. If you don’t have culture, it doesn’t work. Produce a culture by being willing to do anything that anybody in your shop has done.” -Ed Hajim  #SALTTalks

name: SALT
tweet: “Failure early in life is a gift. Doing everything right and having things go wrong is a gift. You learn from that." -Ed Hajim  #SALTTalks

name: SALT
tweet: “No matter what happened to me, I refused to become a victim and I always asked ‘What’s next?’” -Ed Hajim  #SALTTalks

name: SALT
tweet: “If you can truly find someone in life you can support and will support you, who you can share your life with, solves at least half the problem.” -Ed Hajim on his wife Barbara  #SALTTalks

name: SALT
tweet: “15-20 places lived in my first 18 years… the foster homes ranged from cold and abusive to warm and caring… I decided I was going to go to a private college and hide my background and I kept it a secret for 55 years.” -Ed Hajim  #SALTTalks

name: SALT
tweet: "We’re lucky in #Florida that we’re able to be outdoors. Instead of closing beaches, it made sense to open them and [encourage their use] because it kept people outside." -@DeanTrantalis on striking a #COVID public health messaging balance  #SALTTalks

name: SALT
tweet: "Being strangers with one another is the best way to create animosity and maintain an adversarial relationship. Once you reach out and say ‘let’s get to know one another,’ the idea of familiarity helps break down barriers." -@DeanTrantalis  #SALTTalks

name: SALT
tweet: "If you hold onto the past, you’re never going to move forward and grow. It’s important to find commonality, understanding and also acceptance of differences, but it doesn’t mean we have to be adversarial." -@DeanTrantalis on dialogue around #LGBTQ-supportive laws  #SALTTalks

tweet: "I think central banks across the world, especially in the US, have been fairly irresponsible over the past 2-3 decades. They’ve continued to print money at a rate that should raise questions. The use cases for things like #Bitcoin are increasing." -@nikhilkamathcio   #SALTTalks

name: SALT
tweet: “I think we should be careful about how much leverage is provided. When you allow someone with $1 to short $50 worth of #GameStop, that’s when things get unnatural.” -@nikhilkamathcio   #SALTTalks

name: SALT
tweet: "In the entire #GameStop saga, I think it was the #Reddit traders who ended up losing money... They should pick companies that have fundamentals instead of being on the verge of bankruptcy." -@nikhilkamathcio   #SALTTalks

name: SALT
tweet: “Your version of #happiness can’t have a template. Feeling fulfilled in life is something you’ll have to figure out on your own. Trying to have more money than your peer group doesn’t appeal to the newer generation as it did to previous ones.” -@nikhilkamathcio   #SALTTalks

name: SALT
tweet: “I think #education needs to change with the times. People will no longer have one career in which they spend 40 years. I would picture people having 3-4 careers in their lifespan.” -@nikhilkamathcio   #SALTTalks

name: SALT
tweet: "It’s hard to speak truth to power. The only way to make sure people will do it, is to limit power with checks and balances." -@kimballscott   #SALTTalks

name: SALT
tweet: “Bias, prejudice, bullying; There are no organizations in the world where these problems have been eliminated. It’s like staying in shape. They’re things you have to do every day, but they’re worth doing.” -@kimballscott   #SALTTalks

name: SALT
tweet: “We have to be thoughtful about who are the leaders in organizations because they have such a big impact on preventing and mitigating #workplace #injustices.” -@Trier Bryant  #SALTTalks

name: SALT
tweet: “When you lay power on top of #bias or #prejudice, you get #discrimination. Power on top of #bullying, you get #harassment. Power on top of touch, you get physical violation.” -@kimballscott   #SALTTalks

name: SALT
tweet: “The root causes of workplace #injustices are #bias, #prejudice and #bullying. To bring that to life, there are all these things you can think about in your own professional life that contextualize it.” -@Trier Bryant  #SALTTalks

name: SALT
tweet: "It’s not a question of if #China will invade #Taiwan, but when they think they can get away with it." -@joshrogin   #SALTTalks

name: SALT
tweet: “#Biden’s administration has a chance to take the ball and run with it and do a better job. #Trump was great at flipping over the chess board, but he couldn’t set it back up.” -@joshrogin   #SALTTalks

name: SALT
tweet: “I don’t think the goal is to stem #China’s rise. I think the goal is to shape it… It’s going to be a long game. It’s going to last a generation.” -@joshrogin   #SALTTalks

name: SALT
tweet: "The mistake our government made was a large bet that if we gave #China all the help we could and integrated them into our system, China would liberalize economically and then politically." -@joshrogin   #SALTTalks

name: SALT
tweet: “We have to have an actual conversation about the challenges a rising #China presents to our society and figure out what to do about it.” -@joshrogin   #SALTTalks

name: SALT
tweet: “#Credit scores are broken for #Trans people. We’re going into the bureaus and saying, ‘Fix it, please.’ And we’ll show you how to do it.” -@Billie_Simmons_  #SALTTalks

name: SALT
tweet: "#LGBT population spends more than the yearly GDP of Mexico… There’s real money on the table." -@TheBestRob   #SALTTalks

name: SALT
tweet: “An #LGBT person that comes out to their parents has a 40% chance of losing #financial support… LGBT people have on average 50% more #CollegeDebt than the general population.” -@TheBestRob   #SALTTalks

name: SALT
tweet: “An #LGBT couple will have to pay on average $55K to have a child, a cost most non-LGBT couples will not face… This #financial system has not been designed for us. The systemic barriers are huge.” -@Billie_Simmons_, @joindaylight   #SALTTalks

name: SALT
tweet: "It costs more to be #LGBT; When we try to get help, we don’t find it. These things add up so when we look at the long-term #financial outcomes of the #LGBT community, we find their not as strong as the wider community." -@TheBestRob   #SALTTalks

name: SALT
tweet: “20% of #queer people of color are underbanked or unbanked. When you think about the diversity of outcomes our financial community can have, this kind of sensitivity and empathy to live experiences is missing in the financial industry.” -@TheBestRob, @joindaylight   #SALTTalks
